Description.value:
"Breadcrumbs" in the context of web development and navigation refers to a navigational element that consists of a list of links representing the path from the homepage to the current page of a website. This list can be organized hierarchically or chronologically, and its purpose is to help users track their location on the site and easily navigate back to previous levels or pages.

The representation of breadcrumbs might look like this:

Home > Category 1 > Subcategory 1 > Current Page

The "Home" page (the starting point) is usually indicated by the word "Home" or a home icon. Then follows the list of links, each representing a section or category of the website. The last item in the list points to the current page where the user is located.

Breadcrumbs are a useful user interface element that enhances user experience while navigating a website, especially when the site has a complex structure or deep page hierarchy.
